# Legal Shaman Wiki

Full instructions: [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md)

## Folders

Project root: **`~/Projects/legal_shaman`**

- `~/Projects/legal_shaman/raw/` — crawled sources only; never edit manually (use `scripts/` crawlers)
- `~/Projects/legal_shaman/wiki/` — generated knowledge pages
- `~/Projects/legal_shaman/logs/` — ingestion, update, audit, conflict, and maintenance reports

## Core rules

1. The wiki is the system of record — do not re-read `~/Projects/legal_shaman/raw/` when `~/Projects/legal_shaman/wiki/` already has the answer.
2. Preserve source meaning; do not invent legal advice or unsupported conclusions.
3. Every factual claim must trace to source material with visible attribution.
4. Update existing wiki pages before creating new ones; avoid duplicates.
5. Use Obsidian links: `[[Page Name]]`
6. If sources conflict, log in `logs/conflict-report.md` — do not pick silently.

## Answering questions

Wiki-first workflow with required response sections (Answer, Relevant Wiki Pages, Source Documents). See `question-answering.mdc` and [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md#question-answering).

## Ingestion workflow

When processing new/changed `/raw` files: extract topics → update/create wiki pages → add backlinks → update `wiki/index.md` and `logs/ingestion-log.md`.

## Daily updates

Check indexed sources for new/updated/removed/redirected pages. Retired sources: mark retired, log removal, flag affected wiki pages — do not auto-delete wiki pages.
